                        <interp inst="t18360613-name-210" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL JORDAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Gracechurch-street. At half-past three o'clock, on the of June, I was looking behind over London Bridge, and fast a twitch at my pocket—I turned my hand behind me, and caught the pri<lb></lb>soner's hand, and with my left hand I drew my handkerchief from him—I then turned round, and it was the prisoner I had hold of—I collared him and kept him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> The gentleman turned and took hold of me—it was not my hand he had hold of. Witness. I did not leave go of his hand till I turned and took hold of his collar—he asked me particularly to let him go this once.</p>
